post_text: Keeping our Kids Safe in a Digital World presentation will be on Wednesday, January 29 in the Hauser Jr. HIgh AUDITORIUM. Hope you can join us for this important conversation!
text: Keeping our Kids Safe in a Digital World presentation will be on Wednesday, January 29 in the Hauser Jr. HIgh AUDITORIUM. Hope you can join us for this important conversation!

post_text: Keeping our Kids Safe in a Digital World Presentation
text: Keeping our Kids Safe in a Digital World Presentation

post_text:
In partnership with District 96 PTO and PTAs, District 96 welcomes FBI agents Supervisory Special Agent Tara Smith and Special Agent Kassi Hulliberger of the Crimes Against Children/Human Trafficking task force on Wednesday, January 29 at 6:30 PM.

Supervisory Special Agent Smith and Special Agent Hulliberger will deliver a short presentation on how parents can keep their children safe in our digital world as well as answer any questions you may have. If you would like to submit a question anonymously before the presentation, please visit http://bit.ly/D96FBI.
Due to the different topics being discussed during the presentation, we are requesting that children do not attend. Thanks to our PTO and PTAs, child care will be provided for children ages 3 and up.

Date: Wednesday, January 29
Time: 6:30 PM
Location: Hauser Jr. High School LRC

To RSVP for the event, please visit http://bit.ly/D96FBI.
text:

post_text:
District Office Closed August 8 & 9

On Thursday, August 8 and Friday, August 9 our district office will be closed for registration and residency verification. This will allow time for the district office team to relocate and establish services at the new location.

We urge all families who have not yet completed residency verification (required for all new students and students entering Kindergarten, Grade 3 and Grade 6) to complete this process prior to August 8. If this process is not completed by August 8, please plan to complete this process as soon as possible beginning on Monday, August 12 at our new location at 3340 Harlem Avenue.

Registration hours are Monday-Thursday 9am-3pm.
text:

post_text:
Be Seen and Heard 2.0 Parent Information Night
Monday, February 6 at 6:30 PM
In response to the state mandate of educating students about Erin’s Law, Riverside School District 96 will be hosting an assembly called Be Seen and Heard 2.0© - a prevention- oriented child sexual abuse program, for all students. This program is designed to create an age-appropriate, safe and engaging environment where students will learn about the difference between safe and unsafe touch, and the importance of having trusted heroes. Parents are invited and encouraged to attend this special information meeting to preview the concepts of Be Seen and Heard 2.0© program prior to the schools holding the assemblies. Victor Pacini – Author will be available for questions.

post_text:
District Science Showcase

District 96 is hosting a District Science Showcase on Tuesday evening, January 31, 2017 for all fifth and sixth grade students. At this showcase, all students participating in the district science club are expected to present their projects to be judged for an opportunity to participate in the Annual West Suburban Consortium for Academic Excellence (WSCAE) Brookfield Zoo Science Fair on February 23, 2017. The District 96 Science Showcase will be held at Hauser Jr. High from 6:30 - 8:30 PM.

For more information and for club members to register, please click on this link: https://goo.gl/7zKm1M

To see the rubrics that will be used in judging click on the links below:
Science: https://goo.gl/ldMxo0
Engineering: https://goo.gl/RxtThA
